nodes.body: I think these results can go straight into `Adjunction.FullyFaithful`?

Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/4ddf5ea8-817d-4a39-a812-fb1f95327f4d) for commit b37951deadc14508390c737581cc0c2ef95ca466.
There were [no significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/5821f3f1-e009-434b-b3ea-dad66ec37673/to/4ddf5ea8-817d-4a39-a812-fb1f95327f4d) against commit 24e020ad0bec5b5e8056922952f156ad83b3e774.

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8798419737/job/24145383526)
  * [Check all files imported](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8798419737/job/24145382574)
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8798419737/job/24145382866)

The statement and proof are suboptimal:
```lean
variable [L.Faithful] [L.Full]

example : IsIso adj.unit := inferInstance

instance {Y : C} : IsIso (adj.counit.app (L.obj Y)) :=
  isIso_of_hom_comp_eq_id _ (adj.left_triangle_components Y)

lemma isIso_counit_app_of_iso (X : D) (Y : C) (e : X ≅ L.obj Y) :
    IsIso (adj.counit.app X) := by
  rw [NatTrans.isIso_app_iff_of_iso _ e]
  infer_instance
```
(`import Mathlib.CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty` is needed here.)

Maybe make it into an iff?
Something like `IsIso (h.counit.app X) \iff X \in L.essImage`.
Also I think these should go before `Adjunction.restrictFullyFaithful` (that def doesn't belong to this file IMO).
#12363 moves the def to a new file

```suggestion
lemma isIso_counit_app_iff_mem_essImage [L.Faithful] [L.Full] {X : D} :
```
Also you can maybe specialize this into the old lemma if you think this would make it easier to use?
(I personally think this lemma is enough but I'm not the one using it)
